two kiss and join Cadence. Deacon is on tour, while Scarlett is engaged. Before a show, Deacon flashes back to his wedding night with Rayna, where she tells him that despite all they have been through, the two are meant for each other forever and that they're in each other's bloodstreams and will always be there to choose each other forever. Deacon performs and makes up with his dad. As he performs \"A Life That's Good\", the girls and Scarlett join him. As they sing, Gunnar and Will walk out, and then Juliette and Avery with both twins who play Cadence and they all sing the song. Then every previous cast member from the show joins them on stage, such as Jolene, Beverly, Rayna, Teddy, Luke, and more, revealing it is unscripted and [[breaking the fourth wall]] as creator Khouri thanks everyone for a wonderful six years and hopes they all have a life that's good. \n\n'''Songs:''' \"Free\" (sung by Juliette); \"Little Fire\" (sung by Maddie); \u201cDwell in my Soul\u201d (sung by Alannah); \u201cCarolina Rain\u201d (sung by Hallie); \u201cAll That Matters\u201d (sung by Jenny); \u201cHeart\u201d (sung by Daphne); \"A Life That's Good\" (sung by Rayna, Juliette, Deacon, Avery, Scarlett, Maddie, Daphne, Gunnar, and Will)\n| LineColor=#07282F\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Ratings==\n===Nielsen===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| noshare   = y\n| title1   = [[#ep109|New Strings]]\n| date1    = January 4, 2018\n| rs1      = 0.2\n| viewers1 = 0.87<ref name=\"6.01\"/>\n| dvr1     = n/a\n| dvrv1    = n/a\n| total1   = n/a\n| totalv1  = n/a\n\n| title2   = [[#ep110|Second Chances]]\n| date2    = January 11, 2018\n| rs2      = 0.1\n| viewers2 = 0.78<ref name=\"6.02\"/>\n| dvr2     = 0.4\n| dvrv2    = 1.09\n| total2   = 0.5\n| totalv2  = 1.87<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/cable-live-7-ratings-for-jan-8-14-2018/ |title='Nashville' grows by 400 percent in cable Live +7 ratings for Jan. 8-14 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=January 26, 2018 |work=TV by 